Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 1/8/99

Spent most of the time with Wayne trying to come up with a schedule and plan
for Phase 1 of DPI.

After a lot of discussions, we basically come out with the following idea:

DPI will be implemented as a module sitting between the packet bus and the
Demux task.  DPI will accept packets from the bus, perform switching, and
send the packets of the spliced program to Demux.  This way changes to the
current code can be reduced to minimum.

We currently plan to have two tasks in the DPI module, a buffering task
which accepts packets from the bus and put them in the corresponding PID
buffer queue, and a switcher task which is basically a state machine to
perform splicing.

Besides the overall architecture, we have also discussed the following topics:
    - splice command format
    - separation of mixed transport packets
    - DTS/PTS calculation
    - time base adjustment between programs
    - frame alignment problem
    - sequence header capture
    - closed GOP versus open GOP handling
    - null P picture insertion

